OL,3,CAbuse victims holding concealed phone
OL,4,Ccan opt out of emergency alert - Long
OL,6,F"We know that some perpetrators don't
OL,7,Fallow their victims to have a phone,
OL,8,For they monitor and control its use as
OL,9,Fa way to isolate them from family,
OL,10,Ffriends or any kind of support network.
OL,12,F"In these situations, a second secret
OL,13,Fphone can be an important form of
OL,14,Fcommunication; it may even be the only
OL,15,Flifeline they have in an emergency.
OL,17,F"It is possible to deactivate the
OL,18,Falert before it happens and I would
OL,19,Fencourage any domestic abuse survivors
OL,20,Fto take steps to do this before the
OL,21,Ftest happens on 7 September."
